## Anti-example (❌ do NOT capture this kind of entry here)

```
### DEC-XXX — Some users have null names
- Case: nameless users
- Handling: check for null before display
```

**Why this is wrong:** Null-checking display fields is baseline craftsmanship,
not a domain edge case. If "nameless user" is actually meaningful in the
domain (e.g., "guest checkout creates a user with no name until they
register"), then **that's** the case — capture the guest-checkout flow,
not the technical null check.

A good domain edge case explains a **business or regulatory scenario**.
If your entry reads like a code-review nit ("remember to handle empty
strings"), it doesn't belong here.

